1 36–501.
2 (a) A cannabis agent must be registered with the Administration before the agent
3 may volunteer or work for a cannabis licensee or cannabis registrant.
4 (b) A cannabis agent registration is valid for 2 years.
5 (c) (1) [To] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
6 SUBSECTION, TO register as a cannabis agent with the Administration, an individual
7 must:
8 [(1)] (I) be at least 21 years old; and
9 [(2)] (II) if the records are legally accessible, obtain a State and national
10 criminal history records check in accordance with § 36–505 of this subtitle.
11 (2) A CANNABIS AGENT WHO IS EMPLOYED TO PROVIDE SECURITY
12 SERVICES FOR A CANNABIS LICENSEE OR CANNABIS REGISTRANT AS A SECURITY
13 GUARD OR BY A SECURITY GUARD AGENCY, AS DEFINED IN § 19–101 OF THE
14 BUSINESS OCCUPATIONS AND PROFESSIONS ARTICLE, IS NOT REQUIRED TO
15 OBTAIN A STATE OR NATIONAL CRIMINAL HISTORY RECORDS CHECK IN
16 ACCORDANCE WITH § 36–505 OF THIS SUBTITLE IF THE CANNABIS AGENT IS
17 AUTHORIZED TO PROVIDE SECURITY GUARD SERVICES UNDER TITLE 19, SUBTITLE
18 4 OF THE BUSINESS OCCUPATIONS AND PROFESSIONS ARTICLE.
19 (d) (1) The Administration may not register as a cannabis agent an individual
20 who does not meet the criteria established under subsection (c) of this section.
21 (2) The Administration may disqualify an individual from registering as a
22 cannabis agent if the individual has been convicted of or pleaded nolo contendere to a crime
23 involving moral turpitude, whether or not any appeal or other proceeding is pending to
24 have the conviction or plea set aside.
25 (e) The Administration may not deny a cannabis agent registration based on any
26 cannabis–related offenses occurring before July 1, 2023.
27 (f) A cannabis licensee shall require each registered cannabis agent to complete
28 an annual responsible vendor training program authorized under this title.
29 (g) A registration of a cannabis agent issued by the Natalie M. LaPrade Medical
30 Cannabis Commission on or before July 1, 2023, shall:
31 (1) be valid under this title; and

