5 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
6 (k) “Security guard” means an individual who, regardless of whether the
7 individual is described as a security guard, watchman, or private patrolman or by other
8 title:
9 (1) (i) is an employee of a security guard agency; and
10 (ii) provides security guard services to another person on behalf of
11 the security guard agency; or
12 (2) (i) is an employee of a security guard employer; and
13 (ii) provides security guard services to the security guard employer.
14 (l) (1) “Security guard agency” means a person who conducts a business that
15 provides security guard services.
16 (2) “Security guard agency” does not include:
17 (i) a person that is primarily engaged in the business of owning,
18 maintaining, or otherwise managing property; or
19 (ii) a security guard employer.
20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
